            , <rs id="t18291029-186-viclabel1047" type="occupation">carcase-butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-186-victim1476 t18291029-186-viclabel1047"></join>, <placeName id="t18291029-186-crimeloc1048">Harrow-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-186-crimeloc1048" type="placeName" value="Harrow-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-186-crimeloc1048" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-186-off1045 t18291029-186-crimeloc1048"></join>. I saw the pig in Taylor's possession - it is master's, and was stolen out of the sty, where it was put to fatten; I saw it safe about five o'clock the evening before - it was fastened in the sty, which is in a yard: the prisoner has been lurking about there for the last two months.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The pig was given to me by a man who goes about with water-cresses - I know him very well by sight; he told me to go to Kelsal-green, at four o'clock in the morning, and gave it to me to take to Oxford-market.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18291029-186-verdict1049" type="verdictDescription">
